<section class="reliability-card">
  <div class="content">
    <h2>
      35 Years of Field Exposure Proves that BOM Matters
    </h2>

    <p class="intro">
      A recent study of Europe’s first grid-connected solar project, the
      TISO-10-kW plant in Switzerland, demonstrates the profound impact of
      material selection on long-term field performance.
    </p>

    <!-- Quote Section -->
    <div class="quote-container">
    <span class="quote-mark">”</span>

    <div class="quote-body">
        <p class="quote-text">
        PV modules with different encapsulant formulations were exposed to the
        exact same field conditions for thirty-five years. One type of
        encapsulant remains transparent with minimal signs of aging, one is
        aging severely and one only moderately.
        </p>

        <p class="quote-source">
        SOURCE: ÉCOLE POLYTECHNIQUE FÉDÉRALE DE LAUSANNE (EPFL) – PVLAB
        </p>

        <button class="source-toggle" id="openSource">
        SOURCE DETAILS
        </button>

        <div class="source-details" id="sourceDetails">
        <p>
            Annigoni, E, Virtuani, A, Caccivio, M, Friesen, G, Chianese, D, Ballif, C.
            35 years of photovoltaics: Analysis of the TISO-10-kW solar plant,
            lessons learnt in safety and performance—Part 2.
            Prog Photovolt Res Appl. 2019; 27: 760–778.
        </p>
        <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/pip.3146" target="_blank">
            https://doi.org/10.1002/pip.3146
        </a>

        <p>
            Virtuani A, Caccivio M, Annigoni E, Friesen G, Chianese D, Ballif C.
            35 years of photovoltaics: Analysis of the TISO-10-kW solar plant,
            lessons learnt in safety and performance—Part 1.
            Prog Photovolt Res Appl. 2019; 27: 328–339.
        </p>
        <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/pip.3104" target="_blank">
            https://doi.org/10.1002/pip.3104
        </a>
           <!-- COLLAPSE -->
          <div class="collapse-wrapper">
            <button class="source-toggle" id="closeSource">
              COLLAPSE
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const openBtn = document.getElementById("openSource");
  const closeBtn = document.getElementById("closeSource");
  const details = document.getElementById("sourceDetails");

  openBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    details.classList.add("show");
    openBtn.style.display = "none";
  });

  closeBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    details.classList.remove("show");
    openBtn.style.display = "inline";
  });
</script>


